entity-family-3d-solids — ACIS + mesh + curve 3D entity families
================================================================

Status: DEFERRED (schms-parity 1.6.6). Parent: entity-mutation-parity.

Not yet in the entity-family registry (accepted permissively):

  - 3DSOLID, REGION, BODY — ACIS entities; the SAT/SAB stream rides in
    the 1/3 codes (AcDbModelerGeometry, 70 version, 1 .. proprietary
    data). ENTMAKE of these is unusual (normally command-created) but
    the DXF model must round-trip them.
  - SURFACE (plane/extrude/loft/revolve/sweep/nurbs subclasses).
  - MESH (AcDbSubDMesh: 91 subdivision level, 92 vertex count, 93 face
    list, 94 edge count, 95 crease count).
  - POLYGON MESH / POLYFACE MESH variants of POLYLINE (70 bit 16/64;
    the 71/72 mesh MxN counts) — POLYLINE is registered but only the
    2d-polyline subtype is modelled; the mesh subtypes need their own
    vertex-subentity semantics.
  - HELIX (AcDbHelix), and the underlying SPLINE path.

Do
--

Register descriptors, carry the ACIS stream opaquely (round-trip
fidelity, no geometry kernel), model the POLYLINE mesh subtypes and
their VERTEX flavours, add tests. No rendering.

Reference: AutoCAD DXF reference, 3DSOLID/REGION/BODY/SURFACE/MESH/
POLYLINE (mesh)/HELIX.
